          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook and blend",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the {{tinned-tomatoes}}, {{onion}}, {{garlic}}, {{tomato-puree}}, {{stock-vegetable}}, {{olive-oil}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{black-pepper}} to the slow cooker. Stir to combine. Cook on low for 6 hours. Blend smooth using a stick blender directly in the pot. Taste, if the soup is sharp, add the {{granulated-sugar}} and blend again. Swirl in {{double-cream}} to finish if using. Taste and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Add 1 teaspoon of sugar and stir in. Taste again, this usually resolves it. A pinch of bicarbonate of soda also neutralises acidity but use carefully",
              "cause": "Tinned tomatoes vary in sweetness by brand and season",
              "symptom": "Soup tastes sharp or acidic"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Blend uncovered and simmer on high for 20 minutes with the lid off to reduce. Or add a spoonful of tomato purée and blend again",
              "cause": "Too much stock or watery tinned tomatoes",
              "symptom": "Soup too thin after blending"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Blended soups absorb salt differently, season generously after blending. A few drops of red wine vinegar also lifts a flat tomato soup",
              "cause": "Insufficient seasoning or weak stock",
              "symptom": "Soup tastes flat despite a long cook"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Slow-cooker tomato soup is the most hands-off soup you can make. Everything goes in raw, the slow cooker does six hours of work, and a stick blender finishes it in two minutes. Serve with buttered white bread or grilled cheese. Freeze in individual portions for a fast weekday lunch.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
